<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16343] Handle MDC snapshot being null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16343</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using slf4j 2 with the jdk14 adapter, SLF4J uses the NOPMDCAdapter: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.slf4j.org/api/org/slf4j/helpers/NOPMDCAdapter.html.&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.slf4j.org/api/org/slf4j/helpers/NOPMDCAdapter.html.&lt;/a&gt; This always returns null from MDC.getCopyOfContextMap().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In MDCSnapshot.java, there is an assumption that the context map is never null. The SOLRDispatchFilter uses MDCSnapshot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in the following traceback in our project using Solr 8.11.1 up:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
